== Root Cause Analysis ==

The original bug was a TCP iovec use-after-free race in transport_tcp.c where
read and write paths shared a cached iovec buffer. Under concurrent request/response
traffic, the write path could modify the iovec while the read path was still using
it, causing kernel_recvmsg() to read the wrong number of bytes from the TCP stream.

This manifested as:
1. RFC1002 header for SESSION_SETUP authenticate read as 162 bytes (stale value)
   instead of actual 246/252 bytes
2. Server consumed only 162 bytes, leaving 84-90 bytes unread in TCP buffer
3. Next RFC1002 header read got bytes from middle of NTLMSSP auth token
4. Parsed as PDU length 6424065 → exceeded max → connection killed
5. Session setup tolerance code handled the size mismatch gracefully but
   couldn't prevent the stream desync on subsequent reads

The GPT agent's fix: allocate per-call iovec buffer (kmalloc_array + kfree)
instead of reusing shared cached iovec across read/write paths.

