2026-02-28T16:15:00+01:00 | agent=claude | status=smb1-smb202-fixes

== Phase: Fix SMB1 and SMB2.0.2 Until Fully Functional ==

Goal: Fix all remaining SMB1/SMB2.0.2 bugs so all protocol tests pass.

=== Bug 1: SMB2.0.2 Credit Underflow (FIXED) ===

Root cause: In smb2misc.c, the credit charge validation at `validate_credit:`
was gated by `SMB2_GLOBAL_CAP_LARGE_MTU` capability. SMB2.0.2 has
capabilities=0 (no LARGE_MTU), so smb2_validate_credit_charge() was never
called, and outstanding_credits was never incremented on incoming requests.
smb2_set_rsp_credits() then tried to decrement it → underflow.

Fix: Added else branch for non-LARGE_MTU connections that increments
outstanding_credits by 1 per request (SMB2.0.2 always uses single-credit ops).

=== Bug 2: SMB2.0.2 FSCTL_VALIDATE_NEGOTIATE Failure (FIXED) ===

Root cause: smb2_handle_negotiate() had `if (conn->dialect > SMB20_PROT_ID)`
guard for copying ClientGUID and cli_sec_mode. SMB2.0.2 (== SMB20_PROT_ID)
was excluded, leaving these fields zeroed. The FSCTL_VALIDATE_NEGOTIATE_INFO
IOCTL then compared against the client's actual GUID/SecurityMode → mismatch
→ EINVAL → NT_STATUS_INVALID_NETWORK_RESPONSE.

Fix: Changed `>` to `>=` to include SMB2.0.2 in ClientGUID/SecurityMode copy.

=== Bug 3: Pure SMB1 Negotiate Failure - NT_STATUS_INVALID_LOGON_TYPE (FIXED) ===

Two sub-issues:

a) Dialect mismatch: smbclient sends "\2NT LANMAN 1.0" but ksmbd only knew
   "\2NT LM 0.12". Both are valid SMB1/CIFS dialect names for NT1.
   Fix: Added "\2NT LANMAN 1.0" as alternate match in ksmbd_lookup_dialect_by_name().

b) Subsequent SMB1 requests rejected: ksmbd_init_smb_server() had
   `if (proto == SMB1_PROTO_NUMBER) return -EINVAL` when need_neg=false,
   blocking ALL post-negotiate SMB1 requests. Also, conn->need_neg was
   never set to false for SMB1 (only smb2_handle_negotiate did it), causing
   init_smb1_server() to be called repeatedly, leaking conn->vals.
   Fix: Added conn->smb1_conn flag, set need_neg=false in ksmbd_init_smb_server
   init branch, only reject SMB1 on non-SMB1 (upgraded) connections.

=== Bug 4: SMB1→SMB2 Auto-Upgrade IO_TIMEOUT (FIXED) ===

Root cause: When SMB1 NEGOTIATE included "SMB 2.002", the server selected
dialect 0x0202 and put it in the upgrade response. The client interpreted
this as "negotiate complete with 0x0202" and sent SESSION_SETUP directly.
But the server was in NEED_NEGOTIATE state expecting a full SMB2 NEGOTIATE.

Fix: Force conn->dialect = SMB2X_PROT_ID (0x02FF wildcard) in the upgrade
path. This tells the client to send a full SMB2 NEGOTIATE for proper dialect
selection (including SMB2.1, 3.0, 3.11 etc.).

=== Bug 5: conn->vals Memory Leak (FIXED) ===

Root cause: init_smb*_server() functions allocate conn->vals via kmemdup
but never free the previous allocation. This caused leaks when:
- init_smb1_server → init_smb3_11_server (upgrade path)
- init_smb3_11_server (ksmbd_init_smb_server) → init_smb*_server (smb2_handle_negotiate)

Fix: Added kfree(conn->vals) before re-allocation in:
- ksmbd_smb_negotiate_common() upgrade path
- smb2_handle_negotiate() before the dialect switch

